			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2009</a> paper:</span><br><i>ScalaQL: Language-Integrated Database Queries for Scala</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/DanielSpiewak.html">Daniel Spiewak</a>, <a href="../profile/TianZhao.html">Tian Zhao</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_12">10.1007/978-3-642-12107-4_12</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> ScalaQL is an embedded DSL for expressing database queries within Scala.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It relies on embedding/integration with the host language (Scala) as the core mechanism.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3d.html"><span class="tagL">T3D: GPLs</span></a><ul><li> It leverages a general-purpose programming language (Scala) as the host platform for the DSL.
</li></ul></li></ul>
